                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="alfredthegreat_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">(849-99) king of <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/wessex" title="Wessex definition"><span class="ndv">Wessex</span></a> (871-99). He is remembered for defending England against Danish attacks, for establishing the English <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/navy#navy_sng_1" title="navy definition"><span class="ndv">navy</span></a>, and for encouraging education and the use of the English language. There is a popular story of King Alfred and the cakes. After a battle he was hiding in a woman's house. Not knowing who he was, she told him to look after her cakes which were cooking by the fire, and then became very angry when he let them burn.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
